Halve, peel and thinly slice the @red onion{1}(halved, peeled and thinly sliced). Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1}(peeled and grated). Drain and rinse the @black beans{1}(drained and rinsed) in a #sieve{}.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #saucepan{} on medium-high heat. Once the oil is hot, add the onion and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cook until soft, ~{4-5%mins}, stirring occasionally. Stir in the garlic, @chipotle paste{20%g} and @Mexican style spice mix{1}, then cook for ~{1%min}.

> Use less chipotle and/or spice if you don't like too much heat.

Meanwhile, pour the @water{300%ml} for the rice into a medium saucepan with a tight-fitting #lid{}. Stir in the @basmati rice{150%g} and @salt{1/4%tsp} and bring to the boil on medium-high heat. Once boiling, turn the heat down to medium and cover with the lid. Leave to cook for ~{10%mins}, then remove the pan from the heat (still covered) and leave to the side for another ~{10%mins} or until ready to serve (the rice will continue to cook in its own steam).

Pour in the @water{400%ml} for the sauce, then stir in the @vegetable stock paste{10%g}, @sun-dried tomato paste{25%g} and @red split lentils{100%g}. Stir together, bring to the boil, then reduce the heat to medium. Cover with a lid and simmer until the lentils are tender, ~{20-25%mins}. Stir occasionally to ensure the lentils aren't sticking to the bottom of the pan. Add the black beans to the chilli for the final ~{5%mins} of cooking time.

> Add a splash of water if it's a little thick.

While the rice and chilli cook, zest and halve the @lime{1/2}(zested and halved). Quarter the @baby plum tomatoes{125%g}(quartered) and finely chop the @coriander{1}(finely chopped, stalks and all). Squeeze half the lime juice into a medium #bowl{}, then add the @olive oil{1} for the salsa and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Mix together, then add the tomatoes and coriander to the bowl. Stir to combine, then set aside.

When everything is ready, taste the chilli and season with @salt{} and @pepper{} if needed. Fluff up the rice with a fork, then stir through the lime zest and spoon into your bowls. Top with the chilli, a spoonful of the tomato salsa and a dollop of @creme fraiche{75%g}. Cut the remaining lime into wedges for squeezing over. Enjoy!

== Step 3 Modification ==

If you've chosen to add diced chorizo to your meal, add the @?chorizo{60%g}(diced) to the pan when you add the onion. Cook until the onion is soft and the chorizo is starting to brown, ~{4-5%mins}, stirring occasionally. Then continue as instructed.